	(579,760,X'',X'3C6272202F3E0A',X'3C6272202F3E0A',NULL,'\n	Often dated to 1850 because when it burnt down in 1869 it was said to have been restored from the old plans rather than redesigned,. But it does seem it was heavily modified so I have used the lagter date.\n\n	\"Opened in  1850. Burnt down in 1869, the Theatre was restored under the guidance of Vauthier, who deciphered every detail for José Tibúrcio Pereira de Magalhães, the engineer responsible. In 1876 it was reopened: spacious boxes, comfortable seats, sculptures, gilding, chandeliers (one with 152 gas jets), tasseled hangings, a salon with mirrors, jacaranda sofas, so it went on. Not a seat was vacant.\"\n\n	http://www.ctac.gov.br/tdb/english/teatro_santaisabel2.asp\n','\n	Often dated to 1850 because when it burnt down in 1869 it was said to have been restored from the old plans rather than redesigned,. But it does seem it was heavily modified so I have used the lagter date.\n\n	\"Opened in  1850. Burnt down in 1869, the Theatre was restored under the guidance of Vauthier, who deciphered every detail for José Tibúrcio Pereira de Magalhães, the engineer responsible. In 1876 it was reopened: spacious boxes, comfortable seats, sculptures, gilding, chandeliers (one with 152 gas jets), tasseled hangings, a salon with mirrors, jacaranda sofas, so it went on. Not a seat was vacant.\"\n\n	http://www.ctac.gov.br/tdb/english/teatro_santaisabel2.asp\n',X'0A','\n','\n','\n'),
