	(599,780,X'',X'3C6272202F3E',X'3C6272202F3E',NULL,'\n located in a narrow valley in Duong Xuan Thuong village (currently Thuong Ba village, Thuy Xuan Commune, Hue City). It is one of the most beautiful works of royal architecture of the Nguyen dynasty. The tomb lies in a boundless pine forest, 8 km from Hue.\n\n  \n\n  \n\n \"The Mimh Khiem Duong theatre at King Tu Duc\'s tomb has reopened to serve tourists with court music and dance performances after a long break for maintenance, said the Centre for Preservation of the Former Imperial City of Hue on Monday.\n\n The theatre was built in 1886 to hold classical drama performances for the Nguyen royal family and mandarins. It is known as the oldest theatre in Vietnam. (VNA)\"','\n located in a narrow valley in Duong Xuan Thuong village (currently Thuong Ba village, Thuy Xuan Commune, Hue City). It is one of the most beautiful works of royal architecture of the Nguyen dynasty. The tomb lies in a boundless pine forest, 8 km from Hue.\n\n  \n\n  \n\n \"The Mimh Khiem Duong theatre at King Tu Duc\'s tomb has reopened to serve tourists with court music and dance performances after a long break for maintenance, said the Centre for Preservation of the Former Imperial City of Hue on Monday.\n\n The theatre was built in 1886 to hold classical drama performances for the Nguyen royal family and mandarins. It is known as the oldest theatre in Vietnam. (VNA)\"',X'','','',''),
